</div> 
<p><strong>Nightrider Glaive</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Halberds" href="/Halberds" target="">Halberd</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Nightrider Glaive</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>&nbsp;and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for horseback combat based on its size and length. This allows the weapon to keep its power. When on ground, the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Spinning Slash" href="/Spinning+Slash" target="">Spinning Slash</a> can be implemented to make a damaging spin action and deal a follow up&nbsp;attack.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>A jet-black glaive with a blade as weighty as a bludgeon. Weapon of the Night's Cavalry who ride funeral steeds.&nbsp;</em></p> 
 <p><em>This glaive excels at weighty slash attacks that crash into foes, making it a powerful weapon even on horse back.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Nightrider Glaive in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Nightrider Glaive weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Dropped by <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Night's Cavalry" href="/Night's+Cavalry" target="">Night's Cavalry</a>&nbsp;wandering the road between <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=1569&amp;lat=-121.843&amp;lng=61.47438&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=1569&amp;lat=-121.843&amp;lng=61.47438&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">East Raya Lucaria Gate</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=1075&amp;lat=-116&amp;lng=64.2&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=1075&amp;lat=-116&amp;lng=64.2&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Bellum Church</a>. See it on the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=4483&amp;lat=-118.71&amp;lng=64.76&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA" href="/Interactive+Map?id=4483&amp;lat=-118.71&amp;lng=64.76&amp;zoom=8&amp;code=mapA">Elden Ring Map</a>.</li> 
</ul> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Nightrider Glaive Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>: <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Spinning Slash" href="/Spinning+Slash" target="">Spinning Slash</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon can be infused with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a>.</li> 
 <li><strong>Nightrider Glaive</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stones" href="/Smithing+Stones" target="">Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;500</li> 
 <li>R2 Attack is a heavy overhead swing, different from the horizontal slash on most other Halberds</li> 
 <li>It receives S scaling for Strength for Heavy infusion starting from +20 upgrade, making it a good weapon for pure Strength builds.</li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>The Nightrider Glaive can be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a>. Click below for a list of all possible Ashes of War that can be applied to the halberd.</p> 
